annotationA: Rab proteins geranylgeranyltransferase component A; Binds unprenylated Rab proteins, presents it to the catalytic component B, and remains bound to it after the geranylgeranyl transfer reaction. The component A is thought to be regenerated by transferring its prenylated Rab to a protein acceptor (By similarity)
annotationB: Rab GDP dissociation inhibitor; Regulates the GDP/GTP exchange reaction of most RAB proteins by inhibiting the dissociation of GDP from them, and the subsequent binding of GTP
